description: The median length of described SINEs is ca. 250 bp Â±130 bp SD. The canonical SINE has a tRNA 5' end with the internal promoter, a core of unknown function shared with multiple other SINE families, a 3' end identical to that of the LINE responsible for its mobility, and a simple repeat tail. A few SINEs have a LINE-derived internal pol II promoter, and many lack either or both the core and LINE-derived regions.
